{{Quote|You seem worried.''"<br />"''Worried?''"<br />"''The state of seeing large nighthunters lurking in your future.|Ziara and Thrawn|<ref name="Chaos Rising">''[[Thrawn Ascendancy: Chaos Rising]]''</ref>}}
'''Nighthunters''' were nest-residing [[Species|creatures]] that were known to the [[Chiss Ascendancy]] in the [[Unknown Regions]]. The creatures featured in several phrases that compared nighthunters to similarly dangerous subjects. Such phrases were used on numerous occasions by the associates of the [[Chiss]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo|Thrawn]].

==Behavior==
{{Quote|In the meantime, what kind of hellish nighthunter nest have you just kicked over?''"<br />"''A nighthunter nest that I believe will soon be hunting us.|Ba'kif and Thrawn|<ref name="Chaos Rising" />}}
Nighthunters were [[Species|creatures]] that were known of by the [[Chiss]] of the [[Chiss Ascendancy]] in the [[Unknown Regions]]. Residing in nests and [[hunting]] targets, nighthunters were considered to be dangerous, particularly compared to [[whisker]] cubs.<ref name="Chaos Rising" />

==History==
{{Quote|Thrawn, the ''Grayshrike'' has picked up a new nest of nighthunters. Can you offer them some assistance?|Ar'alani|<ref name="Greater Good">''[[Thrawn Ascendancy: Greater Good]]''</ref>}}
Within the Unknown Regions, nighthunters were the subject of several phrases that referenced the danger that the creatures posed. The Chiss [[Senior Captain]] [[Ar'alani|Irizi'ar'alani]] compared [[Senior Commander]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo]]'s worry over backlash regarding his method of saving an [[Unidentified excursion liner|excursion liner]] from the [[atmosphere]] of a [[Unidentified triple-ringed gas giant|gas giant]] to the fear of nighthunters lurking in his future.<ref name="Chaos Rising" />

[[Standard year|Years]] later,<ref name="Chaos Rising" /> around [[19 BBY]],<ref name="Date">The main events of ''[[Thrawn Ascendancy: Chaos Rising]]'', including the mention of nighthunters, must take place around [[19 BBY]], as per ''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]''.</ref> Ziara, by that [[time]] [[Admiral]] Ar'alani, considered the possibility of the [[Mitth family]], perceiving Senior Captain Thrawn to be a liability, intended to metaphorically throw him to the nighthunters by not showing up to his tribunal after he disobeyed orders to achieve victory during a [[Attack on the Paataatus|military engagement]]. [[Supreme General]] [[Ba'kif]] referred to Thrawn's agitation of the [[Nikardun Destiny]] as kicking over a nighthunter nest, while [[Mid Captain]] [[Ufsa'mak'ro]] compared the Chiss Ascendancy, as seen by the [[Nikardun]], to a nighthunter in contrast to the whisker cub that was the [[Lioaoin Regime]].<ref name="Chaos Rising" /> In the [[18 BBY|following year]], during the Ascendancy's [[Nikardun campaigns|campaigns]] to eliminate Nikardun resistance, Ar'alani compared a nighthunter nest to [[Nighthunter (gunboat)|Nikardun missile boats]] attacking Senior Captain [[Irizi'in'daro|Lakinda's]] ''[[Grayshrike]]'', though Lakinda acknowledged that her attackers were more comparable to whisker cubs.<ref name="Greater Good" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Nighthunter.jpg|thumb|right|175px|Nighthunters as they appear in Star Wars Legends]]
In the new ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[canon]], nighthunters were first mentioned in the novel ''[[Thrawn Ascendancy: Chaos Rising]]'', written by [[Timothy Zahn]] and published in [[2020]].<ref name="Chaos Rising" /> In [[Star Wars Legends]], they were first shown in the [[Power of the Jedi Sourcebook]]<ref name="Power of the Jedi">''[[Power of the Jedi Sourcebook]]''</ref> and later appeared in the video game ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]],'' in which they were named "maalraas".<ref name="KOTOR II">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''</ref>

